						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up before the Sakalēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1183, Kārttīka śu. 15, Thursday, corresponding to 1261 A.D., December 8.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 55 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Sakalēśvara Mahādēva of Māmaṁḍala by Baoḍḍavelvi Māra-Bōyuṇḍu, for the merit of Gaṇapamadēvi-Ammaṅgāru.</p>						

						</summary>
